<HEADLINE> Thai Cabinet Approves Additional Budget Cut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet today approved
in principle an additional cut of 50 to 70 billion baht (1.7 to
2.3 billion U.S. dollars) from the 1998 fiscal budget.
</P>
<P>
Government agencies will work together to work out details of
the budget, according to a press release from the Government House
today.
</P>
<P>
The final report will be submitted to the cabinet for approval
on August 17.  
</P>
</TEXT>
