<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two German Soldiers Admit Anti-Foreigner Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Two German soldiers have admitted
setting alight a foreigners' hostel in the eastern German city of
Dresden Saturday because they hate foreigners, investigators said
today.
</P>
<P>
The two recruits, aged 18 and 20, were arrested Sunday and
admitted that they had smeared two swastikas on the building and
then torched it early Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The hostel was burnt out, but nobody was injured because the
inhabitants, Italian construction workers, had gone on vacation
shortly before.
</P>
<P>
The hostel had been the target of an earlier arson attack in
December 1996. Authorities said they were investigating whether
the two soldiers were also involved in that incident.
</P>
<P>
The German Defense Ministry in Bonn meanwhile started its own
investigation into the case and said that the two soldiers would
be punished with the hardest disciplinary measures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
