<HEADLINE> France Backs Resumption of Israeli-Palestinian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- France today expressed its support
for a resumption of dialogue between Israel and Palestinians, and
wished U.S. Middle East coordinator Denis Ross success in his
mediation between the two sides which began last weekend.
</P>
<P>
"A will of dialogue exists, even though the gap is
unfortunately very wide between the positions of one and
another," said French Foreign Ministry spokesman Yves Doutriaux.
</P>
<P>
He said that France "ardently supports" the mission of Ross,
which he said "appears to have a good augury."
</P>
<P>
Palestinian and Israeli security officials met for the first
time Sunday in the presence of Ross, after Israel suspended its
overall contacts with the Palestinians after a terrorist bombing
attack upon a Jewish marketplace in Jerusalem on July 30.
</P>
<P>
Ross, who renewed his peace mission after a four-month
suspension, had persuaded the two sides to resume dialogue in
security matters, which was suspended by the Palestinians to
protest Israeli construction of settlements on Arab land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
