<HEADLINE> DPRK, Switzerland to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) and Switzerland issued a joint communique
here today, declaring that the two countries would strengthen
cooperation in economy and trade.
</P>
<P>
The Korean Central News Agency reported that DPRK Vice
Premier and Foreign Minister Kim Yong-nam met with a delegation
from the Swiss Foreign Ministry, which paid a visit from August 5
to 9 to the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
During its stay in Pyongyang, the Swiss delegation discussed
strengthening bilateral cooperation with superintendents from the
DPRK Agriculture Commission, the Red Cross and other departments.
</P>
<P>
The delegation said the DPRK badly needed international food
aid, and the Swiss government would provide emergency aid and
cooperate with the DPRK in agriculture, animal husbandry and the
cultivation of fruit trees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
