<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Increased UN Fund in Bosnia's Demining Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The UN Mission in Bosnia
(UNMIBH) today appealed to the international community to increase
investment in the demining activities in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
UNMIBH spokesman Alexander Ivanko said that due to the world's
"donor fatigue" towards Bosnia, there is a shortfall of 60 million
US dollars in the UN-organized demining activities in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
For the funding target of 23 million dollars this year, seven
million have been collected so far and only one tenth of the 1,200
people necessary for demining in Bosnia have been trained and
working.
</P>
<P>
"It is extremely important that cash contribution comes as soon
as possible because the demining season in Bosnia is very, very
short" as snow begins to fall in early October, said Ivanko.
</P>
<P>
Since UN demining activities are concentrated in areas where
refugees are returning, the investment for the demining purpose
contributes to accelerating refugees' returns as well as saving
lives, the UN spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
In the more than three years of the Bosnian war up to the end
of 1995, an estimated 3 million mines had been laid by the
country's ethnic foes and only a fraction of them have been
demined.
</P>
<P>
The remaining mines not only hinder the recovery of living in
the country, but cause 60 to 90 casualties every month, according
to UN statistics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
