<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Awards Tanzanian Doctor for Drug Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 11 (Xinhua) -- A Tanzanian doctor, professor
Gad Paul Kilonzo of the Muhimbili Medical Center, today received an
award from the United Nations Drug Control Program (UNDCP) for his
eminent contribution in international drug abuse control.
</P>
<P>
Kilonzo received the award and a cheque of 1,000 U.S. Dollars from
the Nairobi-based UNDCP representative, Kili Luc Kouame, at a
function in Dar es Salaam today.
</P>
<P>
The award was established to honor those who have made
outstanding contribution in the field of international drug abuse
control.
</P>
<P>
Kouame said at the function that the contribution Professor Kilonzo
has made in fighting against drug abuse shows how he is committed to
his country, and other parts of Africa.
</P>
<P>
Kilonzo, also a professor of psychiatry at the University of Dar
es Salaam and the Muhimbili College of Health Science, is the author
of many articles, books and case studies. He has won international
reputation in the field of drug abuse control.  
</P>
</TEXT>
