<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Defense Minister on Military Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Russian Defense Minister Igor
Sergeyev today said the effectiveness, cost and enforceability of
proposed measures and the ability to reach the highest level of
military security in Russia are the main criteria of military
reform.
</P>
<P>
According to a report of the Itar-Tass news agency reaching
here from Khabarovsk, Sergeyev, speaking before the officers and
command of the Far Eastern military district today, outlined the
concept of army development and military reform in the country.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev said that the concept consists of "seven
interconnected parts."
</P>
<P>
The first part addresses Russia's military security, the
minister said. A strategic forecast indicates that "a direct
military threat to Russia is not probable in the immediate future
until 2005, while the state of strategic nuclear forces, provided
their combat readiness is maintained at the required level, is
sufficient to respond to the threats which may arise."
</P>
<P>
This period, Sergeyev said, should be used to carry out
military reform to make the country's armed forces efficient,
mobile, well equipped and supported and affordable for the
economy.
</P>
<P>
The second and third parts determine the optimum level of
defense spending by considering economic, demographic and other
resources, as well as combat parameters of the armed forces with a
military budget of 3.5 percent of GDP.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that at the first stage of reform (up to
2000), "we will have to work in conditions of limited financing
and will have to look for ways to economize."
</P>
<P>
In 1997 and subsequent years, the army will be reduced to 1.2
million, but its combat readiness should remain unaffected,
Sergeyev said.
</P>
<P>
At the second stage of reform (until 2005), the armed forces
will be reorganized to leave only three fighting services covering
operations on the land, in the air and at sea.
</P>
<P>
He also outlined measures to improve the system of management,
and reorganize the structure of technical support, military
training, and social welfare support for the military.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev said that Russia has entered the stage of practical
implementation of endorsed measures for the military reform.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
