<HEADLINE> 60 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces today
killed 60 rebels of the Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) during
several military operations in southeastern Turkey, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a statement issued by the office of the
Emergency Regional Rule as saying that in the operations to
sweep PKK militants from the region, 50 PKK members were killed
on Mount Ikiyaka near Hakkari province while another two were
killed in the village of Oyuklu in Diyarbakir province.
</P>
<P>
Eight PKK guerrillas were also killed in the operation in
Pervari in Siirt province, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
It added that two soldiers of the Turkish security forces
died and 11 others were wounded during the operations in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Five PKK members surrendered to the security forces in
several provinces of the southeast, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
More than 27,000 people, including PKK rebels, civilians and
government troops, have been killed in conflicts since the PKK
started a separatist war for autonomy in eastern and
southeastern Turkey in August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
