<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets With US Representatives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIDAIHE, August 12 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislator, Qiao
Shi, in a meeting with members of the US House of
Representatives' International Relations Committee led by its
chairman Benjamin Gilman, said today that their visit will play
an active role in enhancing mutual understanding and promoting
Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, who is the chairman of the Chinese National People's
Congress Standing Committee, said that the Chinese side hopes the
US Congress and its members can play a constructive role in
bilateral ties and that the two powers have major responsibilities
for world peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
Improving bilateral relations is not only in the fundamental
interests of both countries and their people, he said. It is also
conducive to maintaining and promoting peace, stability, and
development in the region and in the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi also noted that China attaches great importance to
Sino-US relations and gives them top priority in its
foreign relations.
</P>
<P>
And there has been momentum in improving bilateral relations
since the beginning of the year, he said, and more exchanges in
various areas, while bilateral economic and trade co-operation has
continued to grow steadily. Many US government leaders and
congressmen have visited China since the beginning of this this
year, Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin's state visit to the US this fall is
significant for bilateral ties for the 21st century, Qiao went on
to say, and the two sides should seize the current favorable
opportunities and follow the three Sino-US communiques to increase
co-operation and narrow differences to promote a healthy and
stable advances of Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also briefed the US representatives on China's stance on
the Taiwan and Tibet issues and on the country's reforms,
opening-up, and the economy.
</P>
<P>
Gilman said that the US Congress is interested in increasing
exchanges and co-operation with China's NPC to contribute to
US-China relations, and that the US side places importance on
China's role in the Asia-Pacific region and in international
affairs.
</P>
<P>
The US guest said the two countries should establish closer
bilateral relations and that the US side hopes to work with the
Chinese in promoting peace, stability and prosperity throughout
the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
