<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Tallest Tower Under Construction in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia today began the
construction of the world's tallest tower -- the Jakarta Tower
here with a ceremony officiated at by Minister/State Secretary
Moerdiono.
</P>
<P>
To arise on a 40,550-square-meter plot of land in the former
Kemayoran Airport area, the tower will be 558 meters high,
surpassing the height of a similar tower in Kuala Lumpur of
Malaysia (421 meters), the Shanghai Tower in China (460 meters)
and the Toronto Tower in Canada (553 meters), the official Antara
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The tower was designed by East China Architecture Design and
Research Institute (ECADI) in Shanghai, China.
</P>
<P>
The construction work of the multi-purpose building is expected
to finish in 2001 and it will serve as a center for multi-media
and broadcasting activities, recreation, trade and international
tourism, Chief of the Jakarta Tower Development Project
Sudwikatmono said at the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Head of the Jakarta Architecture Council Prof. Danisworo said
the Jakarta Tower was designed to withstand earthquakes measuring
up to seven on the Richter scale.
</P>
<P>
Moerdiono said the project would be a contribution to Jakarta
as an international city for meetings of the coming ASEAN Free
Trade Area (AFTA) in 2003 and Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation
(APEC) in 2020.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Tourism, Post and Telecommunication Joop Ave said
that the tower would become a landmark of Jakarta as well as
Indonesia, which was expected to be able to draw millions of
tourists every year.
</P>
<P>
He said Indonesia expected to receive around 11 million foreign
tourists in the year 2005 and earn up to 15 billion U.S. dollars.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
