<HEADLINE> OANA General Assembly Opens in Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The 10th general assembly of the
Organization of Asia-Pacific News Agencies (OANA) opened here
today to explore ways to enhance the vitality to the organization
in the new world situation.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony of the three-day conference was presided
over by OANA President Guo Chaoren, who is also president of
China's Xinhua News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Addressing senior officials from 31 news agencies of 24
countries, Guo said that Asia-Pacific has become a region with
fastest economic growth and strongest development in the world.
</P>
<P>
"This has prepared the region increased information flow,
including further development of all news agencies in the
Asia-Pacific region, and opens up bright prospects for the
cooperation among them," he added.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he said, all OANA members should enhance
cooperation and mutual trust, transcend differences and expand
common understanding so as to make common efforts for the growth
of OANA, for breaking the information monopoly by few, and for
establishing an objective and fair new international information
order.
</P>
<P>
Iran's First Vice-President Hassan Habibi attended the opening
ceremony to extend his congratulations on the holding of the
assembly.
</P>
<P>
Habibi called for close cooperation among the OANA member news
agencies and efforts to maintain accuracy of facts during
reporting in order that they can play an important role in
politics, economy and culture.
</P>
<P>
He cautioned the big news agencies with strong financial
strength against practicing monopoly of news and imposing their
culture, religion and value on the people of other nationalities.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three years, OANA has been expanding steadily and
its international influence has been growing. Since its 1995
general assembly in Beijing, Kaz-TAG of Kazakhstan, KABAR of
Kyrgyztan and AAP of Australia have officially admitted.
</P>
<P>
OANA has also enhanced exchanges and cooperation with news
agencies of Syria, Kuwait, Qatar and other countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
As host of the assembly, Fereydoun Verdinejad, managing
director of the Islamic Republic News Agency of Iran (IRNA),
extended welcome to all delegates and pledged that IRNA would try
to fulfill OANA's all objectives and obligations.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the opening ceremony, Iran's First Vice-President
Habibi met with Guo Chaoren and held friendly talks with him.
</P>
</TEXT>
