<HEADLINE> Hungarian Foreign Trade Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Hungary's exports were worth
8.624 billion U.S. dollars in the first half of this year, 15.1
percent up from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Ministry of Industry, Commerce and Tourism
said today that imports were 9.769 billion dollars, an increase of
13.8 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Hungary's main exports are machinery and processed goods, and
its imports mainly processed goods, machinery, food and raw
materials.
</P>
<P>
Germany is still Hungary's most important trade
partner. Hungary's exports to the United States, Austria, Slovenia
and Poland all increased by more than 30 percent in the first half
of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
