<HEADLINE> Flood Children Holiday in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- About 150 children from the
hardest-hit areas of the recent flooding in Poland and the Czech
Republic have been invited to Germany for two weeks holiday, the
German Foreign Ministry announced today.
</P>
<P>
The children, aged 12 to 16, will go to the southern German
resort of the Black Forest on August 15 to spend vacations with
German children.
</P>
<P>
Poland, the Czech Republic as well as eastern Germany suffered
huge damage in the worst flood of the century in central Europe.
</P>
<P>
As floodwaters receded in recent few days, authorities were
beginning to deal with the arduous task of cleaning up and
rebuilding in the flooded areas. 
