<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Petrochemical Giant Raises Funds in Stock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Jinzhou Petrochemical Co.
Ltd. issued 100 million new A shares on the Shenzhen Stock
Exchange today to raise 461 million yuan in funds, or about 55.5
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The five million-sq.m. company is located in northeast China's
Liaoning Province and handles most petroleum products like
gasoline, diesel fuel, kerosene, solvents, and liquefied petroleum
gas.
</P>
<P>
It also produces major chemicals like isopropyl alcohol,
polypropylene, butadiene rubber, and all kinds of benzene. The
isopropyl alcohol produced by the company has about 80 percent of
the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
The company has over four billion yuan (482 million US dollars)
in sales volume and 700 million yuan in revenues and is 70th of
China's 500 largest businesses.
</P>
<P>
Funds from the listing will be used for the construction of 13
projects, with the focus on new chemical products, according to
company's officials, who said that the factory is working to push
the refining capacity of imported crude to 1.5 million tons
annually.
</P>
<P>
The Board of Directors also expected a net profit this year of
178 million yuan, or nine percent rise. The company has issued 600
million shares as of this listing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
