<HEADLINE> Indonesian Minister Analyses Investment Prospects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The investment prospects in
Indonesia are encouraging in the years to come, notably during the
second long-term development drive (1994-2019), a senior official
said today.
</P>
<P>
"The political, social and economic stability, as well as the
abundant natural resources in the country will support the
investment prospects," Minister for Investment Sanyoto
Sastrowardoyo said at a discussion with entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
He said the factors which would bolster the prospects are big
market in Indonesia, increasing buying power, competitive labor
wages, conducive business climate and strategic location of the
country.
</P>
