metal, electronic industries as well as electric devices and
agricultural products will also attract investors, the minister
said.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian government approved domestic investors to make
2,632 projects with a total investment of 282.5 trillion rupiah
(113 billion U.S. dollars) from April 1, 1994 to July 15, 1997.
</P>
<P>
It also permitted foreign investors to do some 2,558 projects
with a total investment of 110.5 billion U.S. dollars during the
same period. 
