<HEADLINE> Bears Kill Two in Eastern Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Bears mauled two people to death
recently in the far eastern region of Russia.
</P>
<P>
A report said the first tragedy happened in Majadan district
last Wednesday when a man, who left his house near forests to
collect mushrooms, was attacked by a brown bear 500 meters away
and bitten to death.
</P>
<P>
The second attack took place in Khabarovsk district last
Thursday when a 50-year-old woman collecting berries in the forest
fell prey to a bear.
</P>
<P>
This region of Russia witnesses attacks by wild animals on
people every year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, a Japanese photographer was mauled to death by a
bear in Kamchatka district. A man was killed and a woman was
seriously injured in a tiger attack in the Maritime of Primorye
district. 
</P>
