<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungarian Population Older, Smaller </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Hungarian population
decreased to 10.17 million in January 1997, from 10.71 million in
1980, and the population is increasingly becoming aged.
</P>
<P>
Statistics of the Hungarian Central Statistics Bureau show that
in the past 17 years, the Hungarian population has dropped year by
year, with an accumulative amount of more than 500,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the age structure is changing drastically. In 1980,
Hungary had a population under 14 of 2.34 million, which accounted
for 22 percent of the entire population. But now, the number has
dipped to 1.8 million, accounting for 18 percent of the whole
population.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the population aged over 60 has increased to 1.98
million, accounting for 19.5 percent of the entire population,
from 1.83 million in 1980, which accounted for 17 percent of the
whole population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
