<HEADLINE> Nepali Speaker to Resign: Sources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Ram Chandra Poudyal is to
resign as speaker of the Lower House of Nepal, sources close to
Poudyal said today.
</P>
<P>
Poudyal, who is considered among the second-generation
leadership of the main opposition Nepali Congress (NC), wants to
leave his current post so he can get involved in party affairs,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
He wants to strengthen the NC party, which suffered a
humiliating defeat in the recent local polls, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
His resignation will be accepted by the NC, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Poudyal, 54, was elected speaker in the 1994 mid-term polls.
</P>
