<HEADLINE> Mongolia Studies Conference Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The 7th international
Conference on Studies of Mongolia began here today with the
attendance of about 260 foreign scholars from 26 countries, and
more than 100 local scholars.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony, at a local hotel, was sponsored by Ozawa,
a Japanese expert on the studies of Mongolia and the chairman of
the International Federation of the Studies of Mongolia. Mongolian
President Nachagyn Bagabandy also addressed the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, the participants will discuss their
achievements in research on Mongolian history, language,
culture, art, politics, economy, law and philosophy.
</P>
<P>
They will also talk about the development of modern Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
The first International Conference on the Studies of Mongolia
was held in Ulan Bator in 1959. 
</P>
