<HEADLINE> Swedish Media Receives Threat of Bombs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 12 (Xinhua)-- A number of Swedish media
offices have received letters threatening further bomb attacks to
prevent Sweden bidding for the 2004 Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The letters, all signed in the name of "We who built Sweden,"
said it is wrong to spend an enormous amount of money in staging
the Olympic Games while spending for health care, social welfare
and education is reduced.
</P>
<P>
"We who built Sweden" also assumes responsibility for the
recent bomb explosion at Stockholm Stadium, and fires at various
sports arenas in the Stockholm region during the spring and early
summer.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Swedish media received letters signed in
the same way last Christmas, warning of bomb blasts during the
Christmas shopping season. 
</P>
