<HEADLINE> Indonesia Enjoys Trade Surplus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia enjoyed a trade
surplus of 970.7 million U.S. dollars in May as its exports
reached 4.588 billion dollars and its imports came to only 3.617
billion dollars, a senior official said here today.
</P>
<P>
"This is the highest we have achieved in the past four and a
half years," Minister of Industry and Trade Tungky Ariwibowo said
after meeting with President Soeharto at the Bina Graha
Presidential Office.
</P>
<P>
In May, Indonesia exported 3.6 billion dollars worth of
non-oil/gas commodities and 980.1 million dollars worth of oil and
gas, he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister also said the country's exports from January to
May this year reached a total of 21.14 billion dollars, consisting
of 15.94 billion dollars worth of non-oil/gas commodities and 5.2
billion dollars worth of oil and gas.
</P>
<P>
The country's imports over the same period was recorded at 17.8
billion dollars, consisting of 16.17 billion dollars worth of
non-oil/gas commodities and 1.6 billion dollars worth of oil and
gas, he added.
</P>
<P>
Tungky said that the increase in exports came from various
products, like textile and textile products, wood products and
electronics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
