<HEADLINE> UN Envoy on Afghanistan Due in Pakistan Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 12 (Xinhua) -- UN Special Envoy Lakhdar
Brahimi will arrive here Friday to begin his short-term mission of
assessing the UN peacemaking efforts in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Brahimi will consult with interested and relevant countries and
parties in the region, including the Organization of Islamic
Conference, regarding their positions on the UN efforts for peace
in Afghanistan, said the UN Special Mission to Afghanistan (UNSMA)
in a press release issued here today.
</P>
<P>
Brahimi, who was appointed by UN Secretary General Kofi Annan
as his special envoy on Afghanistan early this month, will submit
an in-depth report to Annan for the UN further actions for peace
in the war-torn country, the UNSMA said.
</P>
<P>
While in the region, Brahimi will hold talks with senior
Pakistani officials and religious leaders and he will also meet
with Afghan leaders in and outside Afghanistan, it said.
</P>
<P>
The head of the UNSMA, Norbert Holl, earnestly appeals to the
warring Afghan factions for ceasefire especially during the
Brahimi mission in the next two weeks and requests cooperation by
all concerned to make this mission a success, it said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
