<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Slip Lower on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to slip
lower on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index fell 0.4 points to close at 1893.46 today,
marking again the lowest level in four years.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume stood at 214.08 million units, worth 386.77
million Singapore dollars (about 264.91 million U.S. dollars).
Advances overtook declines by 178 to 133, while 299 other counters
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Hotung was again the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 68.09 million units. It was followed by
the Asian Food &AMP; Properties which had 11.85 million shares traded.
The Hong Kong Land was next with 4.47 million shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose 1.2 dollars to finish at 32 Singapore dollars.
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign increased 70 cents to
end at 26.5 Singapore dollars, while the Singapore Airlines (SIA)
Foreign gained 50 cents to close at 12.1 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Samanda Holdings was the biggest loser as it
declined 90 cents to end at eight Singapore dollars. MISC Foreign
lost 82 cents to close at 2.98 dollars, while Cerebos was 35 cents
lower at 5.1 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
