<HEADLINE> Book Detailing Yangtze River Source Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A book on the scenery, local
customs, religions, culture, and ecology and environment of the
Yangtze River, China's longest, was released in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
"The Soul of the Yangtze River -- Diary of an Explorer at the
Yangtze River Source" is the work of Yang Xin, who has been to the
river's source six times. In the book, the author tells his
experiences along the river, particularly to the river source.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yuqing, deputy-director of the National Environmental
Protection Agency, said during the release ceremony that the book
gives people a better understanding of the Yangtze River and the
environment at its source.
</P>
<P>
The book goes on sale nationwide today and all profits will be
used to build an environmental protection center at the river's
source.  
</P>
