<HEADLINE> Indian PM Upbeat About Indo-Pakistan Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister Inder
Kumar Gujral said he was confident the talks between India and
Pakistan would succeed and that the two neighboring countries
would find a way out on the disputed Kashmir issue, local media
reported today.
</P>
<P>
"Since my talks with Pakistan Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif (in
the Maldives in May), I am optimistic that we will find a way
out," Gujral said in an interview with the BBC to be telecast on
India's Independence Day on August 15.
</P>
<P>
