<HEADLINE> Athens Medalist Jayasinghe Welcomed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Sprinter Susanthika Jayasinghe
received a warm welcome Tuesday when she returned from Athens
where she took the 200 meters silver at the world championships
last week.
</P>
<P>
Jayasinghe, only the second Sri Lankan in nearly 50 years to
grab a medal in a major world championship, was driven in a convoy
of vehicles while thousands of people lined the streets from the
airport to cheer her with flags and banners.
</P>
<P>
The only other Sri Lankan to ever win a medal was Duncan White,
who picked up the silver in 400 meters hurdles at the 1948
Olympics in London.
</P>
<P>
Jayasinghe clocked 22.39 seconds to win her medal, beating
Jamaican veteran Merlene Ottey to third. Ukrainian Zhanna
Pintussevich claimed the title.  
</P>
