<HEADLINE> Outward Processing Contributes to Hong Kong's Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Outward processing related
trade has taken a lion's share of the total imports and exports
between Hong Kong and the Chinese inland areas.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter of 1997, 48 percent of Hong Kong's total
exports to the inland areas were for outward processing, hitting
51.3 billion HK dollars (6.6 billion US dollars), the latest
government figures show.
</P>
<P>
The Census and Statistics Department reported today that
outward processing in the first quarter of this year contributed
to 75 percent of Hong Kong's total imports from the inland areas,
totaling 96.8 billion HK dollars (12.5 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of Hong Kong's re-exports of origin from the inland provinces,
85 percent, or 121.2 billion HK dollars (15.6 billion US dollars)
worth of goods, were related to outward processing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
