<HEADLINE> Dengue Fever Spreads in South Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Dengue fever, which is sweeping
Vietnam's southern Mekong Delta, has killed 90 people so far in
this rainy season, the English language newspaper Vietnam News
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Tra Vinh Province topped the list with 5,071 dengue cases and
43 dengue-related deaths, three times more than the same period
last year while Ca Mau Province reported 4,600 cases and 12
deaths.
</P>
<P>
Kien Giang Province announced 25 deaths out of 2,855 cases. Soc
Trang province had over 800 cases and four deaths. Can Tho
Province had 966 cases and six deaths caused by the disease.
</P>
<P>
Most of the patients were children.
</P>
<P>
Local hospitals and agencies have been mobilized to treat the
patients while distributing insecticides to kill mosquitos which
transmit the cholera-like disease, particularly during rainy
season.
</P>
<P>
Doctors are urging all residents in the southern region to use
mosquito nets to avoid contracting the disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
