<DOCNO> XIE19970812.0148 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest China Province Enhancing Cooperation with Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong has become the biggest
trading partner of Yunnan Province in southwest China, with annual
exports to Hong Kong accounting for nearly a quarter of the
province's annual total.
</P>
<P>
Imports from Hong Kong account for 15 percent of the province's
total annual imports, and Hong Kong investment in Yunnan has
reached 714 million US dollars, accounting for 45 percent of the
total overseas investment in the province.
</P>
<P>
In the past six years, Yunnan has exported 1.63 billion US
dollars worth of agricultural, nonferrous metal, and chemical
products to Hong Kong and imported 430 million US dollars worth of
goods from Hong Kong, almost four times the amount from 1950 to
1988 combined.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong businessmen set up the first joint venture there in
1985, and there are 639 Hong Kong-funded projects now in Yunnan,
26 of which have more than 10 million US dollars each in capital.
</P>
<P>
The province also plans to get more capital from Hong Kong to
help promote the tourist industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
