<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Villagers in Three Gorges Area Welcome Resettlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Yanghe Village will be covered
by water by 2009 when China's Three Gorges Project goes into full
operation, and over 50 percent of its villagers have moved to new
homes ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
They want to start a new life as soon as possible, and the
government has paid enough money for compensation and early
relocation.
</P>
<P>
The villagers say that their village head has given them an
attractive idea for early migration: before 2009, they can start
to cultivate new land, while continuing to work on existing
farmland.
</P>
<P>
According to local government officials, each of the resettlers
will receive some 2,000 yuan from the central government to build
a new residence, with a per-capita living space equal to that of
the old home.
</P>
<P>
At present, 78 of the 134 households in the village have moved
to the new place where per-capita living space is 25 sq m, twice
as much as the country's urban residence average.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Project is the largest hydro-electric power
program in the world. A total of 36,700 ha. of land, five county
seats, and three cities will be wholly or partly submerged, and
more than a million people are expected to be relocated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
