<HEADLINE> ADB to Provide Loans to Support Thailand's Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
will provide about 1.2 billion US dollars over the next three
years to support Thailand's economic stabilization program being
undertaken with the assistance of the International Monetary Fund
(IMF).
</P>
<P>
ADB President Mitsuo Sato said in a news release today the Thai
economy was fundamentally strong and he was confident that
effective implementation of the stabilization program will help
overcome current economic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the IMF agreement to strengthen the banking and
financial system, control inflation, reduce the current account
deficit and maintain fiscal discipline will re-establish
conditions for sustained economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Implementation of the stabilization program will also help
restore the confidence of international and domestic investors, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The Manila-based bank has lent 3.82 billion US dollars to
Thailand for 73 loans since 1968.  
</P>
