<HEADLINE> China's Largest Sea-Railway Container Terminal in Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A railway station for
transporting goods from both ocean-going and railway containers
opened for business Monday in the port city of Qingdao.
</P>
<P>
Believed to be the largest of its kind in China, the facility is
designed to raise efficiency and cut costs by combining the
previously separated operations of railway and ocean container
shipping.
</P>
<P>
Funding for the project came from the Jinan Railway
Administration and the Qingdao Port Authority.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao, in east Shandong Province, is China's first transit
port for international containers. It handled over 800,00 standard
containers (TEU) last year and expects to receive over one million
containers this year. 
</P>
