<HEADLINE> Meeting on European Security to Be Held in Lithuania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Russia and seven other countries
from the central and East Europe will hold a two-day meeting on
European security beginning on September 5 in Vilnius, capital of
Lithuania, the Russian Interfax news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Attending the meeting will be the presidents of Lithuania,
Latvia, Estonia, Poland, Belarus, Ukraine and Finland as well as
Russian Prime Minister Stepanovich Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is called to exchange views on the topic --
coexistence and good neighborly relations among the peoples of
Europe: a guarantee of European security and stability.
</P>
<P>
The leaders will discuss the influence of good neighborliness
among European nations upon European security and stability and
sign a joint declaration on the issue.
</P>
<P>
They will also issue a statement on the reconciliation of
European countries after World War II and the prospects for their
future cooperation.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, representatives from the European Union and
the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe will also
speak on the role of international organizations and institutions
in creating security and stability in Europe. 
