<HEADLINE> Snake Showplace Built in Northern Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- In the mountain area in northern
Fujian Province, the newly-built Snake Culture City is snagging
the interest of tourists, researchers and people who buy and sell
the reptile.
</P>
<P>
Located in Shaowu, the snake exhibition hall houses over 1,000
live snakes in more than 40 species, and over 100 varieties of
stuffed snakes.
</P>
<P>
Coastal Fujian in east China is famous for its snakes. Another
name for Fujian, "min," means "breeding snake." Local people
worshiped snakes in ancient times.
</P>
<P>
Some types of snake are served as delicacies in Chinese dishes.
</P>
<P>
Yet to be built at the snake showplace are restaurants and a
factory that manufactures tonic made from snake parts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970812.0167 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore's Manufacturing Output Up in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's manufacturing
output increased by 9.3 percent in June over the same month of
last year, helping alleviate the decline in the previous months,
which led to a cumulative decline of 1.1 percent for the first six
months of this year, the Economic Development Board (EDB) said
today.
</P>
<P>
It said that export orders boosted output of electronics
products and components by 11.8 percent against the figures of
June last year.
</P>
<P>
However, cumulative output of the electronics sector in the
first half of this year was 2.4 percent less than the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Output of the transport equipment increased by 15.2 percent as
both marine and aviation segments recorded increases in June.
</P>
<P>
Cumulative output for the first six months of 1997 gained 1.5
percent over the corresponding period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The output of the chemical industries, including petroleum,
petrochemicals, pharmaceuticals and industrial/specialty chemicals
industries, increased by 26.2 percent in June, contributing to the
cumulative output growth of 9.7 percent for the first six months
of 1997 over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The petrochemicals industry expanded further as a new cracker
plant came on stream.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the June output increased by 70.9 percent, leading
to the cumulative output increase of 39.1 percent for the first
half of the year, the EDB said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
