<HEADLINE> US's Eaton To Make Truck Transmissions in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Eaton Corporation of the
U.S. will set up a wholly-owned company in Shanghai to manufacture
heavy-truck transmissions for Asia-Pacific markets.
</P>
<P>
Eaton views the deal as part of its long-term strategy to make
10 billion US dollars in sales annually by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The Eaton Truck and Bus Components (Shanghai) Company will be
located in the Pudong New Area and cover a floor space of 100,000
square feet. It is scheduled to go into operation early next year
and is expected to form an annual production capacity of more than
24,000 units by the year 2008.
</P>
<P>
Eaton currently has three joint ventures in China: two are
located in Shandong Province in the east, both producing hydraulic
motors and washing machine control units; and the other, in
Jiangsu Province, also in the east, makes protection devices for
electrical circuits. 
</P>
