<HEADLINE> AIDS Kills 0.4 million Ugandans Since 1988 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- More than 0.4 million Ugandans
have been killed by AIDS since 1988, a local newspaper reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Elizabeth Madraa, program manager of the sex transmitted
disease (STD) AIDS control program, told "the New Vision" Monday that
460,785 of total 546,173 AIDS patients in Uganda have died in the
past 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Madraa added that Ugandans live with HIV virus now number
1,460,767. But a survey conducted in the country in 1988 showed
that the figure was estimated at two millions. 
</P>
