<HEADLINE> Lebanon's First Lung Transplantation Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Gaodeis Hospital here
announced today that doctors has carried out successfully the
first lung transplantation operation for a woman in Lebanon, the
Daily Star newspaper here reported today.
</P>
<P>
This success is not only the first time for Lebanon, but also
for the middle east.
</P>
<P>
The woman, 30, mother of a four-year-old child, had been
suffering from lung fibrosis, as a result her respiratory system
could not work properly and she was always in a weak condition.
</P>
<P>
On August 8, The hospital successfully performed the
operation, which lasted 48 hours, on the woman for transplanting
two parts of her father's lung.
</P>
<P>
Now, the woman and her father are in good health, the
hospital said. 
