<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Improve Telecom Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania plans to install
automatic telephone exchanges with a capacity of 34,504 exchange
lines in rural areas to improve countrywide telecommunications
services.
</P>
<P>
This plan was revealed by public relations officer of the
Tanzania Tele-communications Company Ltd (TTCL) Issa Semtawa
recently.
</P>
<P>
The local press today quoted Semtawa as saying that the plan
will involve the replacement of all manual telephone exchanges
and installation of new telephone exchanges in areas where
telecommunication facilities are non-existent.
</P>
<P>
TTCL is looking for funds to implement the project, according
to Semtawa.
</P>
<P>
The telecommunication sector of Tanzania is currently
undergoing a major improvement under the on-going
telecommunication restructuring program, a five-year
comprehensive investment program aimed at full rehabilitation,
modernization and expansion of the existing telecommunication
network in the country. 
