<HEADLINE> S. Africa Signs Olympic Agreement with Netherlands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 11 (Xinhua) -- South Africa signed an
Olympic agreement with the Netherlands here on Monday to promote
its preparation for the 2000 Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was inked by the National Olympic Committees of
both sides on behalf of their respective countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the Netherlands is expected to help South
African athletes prepare for the 2000 Games.
</P>
<P>
"The agreement covers both elitist and developmental aspects
with special coaching clinics being held in South Africa and
participation opportunities for our sporting codes in the
Netherlands," said Dan Moyo, secretary-general of the South
African committee.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands enjoyed expertise as Olympic champions in field
hockey, men's volleyball, mountain cycling and rowing, as well as
being one of the world's top footballing nations.
</P>
<P>
Wim de Heer, acting secretary general of the Netherlands
National Olympic Committeee, said that "we are keen to help South
Africa continue its nation-building progress through Olympism."
