<DOCNO> XIE19970812.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1950 Treaty With India Should Be Reassessed: Nepali FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Foreign Minister Kamal
Thapa has said that the 1950 Treaty of Peace and Friendship
between Nepal and India should be reassessed in the changing
context of regional security and new international order, the
daily Rising Nepal reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to the Letter of Exchange attached with the treaty,
"neither government shall tolerate any threat to the security to
the other by a foreign aggression. To deal with any such threat
the two governments shall consult with each other and devise
effective counter measures."
</P>
<P>
But Nepal was not consulted as per the provisions, Thapa said.
</P>
<P>
Likewise, Indian Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral has also
reiterated that India will not seek any reciprocity with any
neighboring countries in the changed context of world politics, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"The 1950 treaty should therefore be reviewed as in the new
context as have reached many agreements like Trade and Transit,
SAPTA (South Asian Preferential Trading Arrangement) and Power
trade, " Thapa said.
</P>
<P>
The treaty has come under sharp criticism from all sides in
Nepal in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Critics say some of the treaty's clauses infringe upon Nepal's
sovereignty and fail to reflect the present-day realities as well.
</P>
<P>
While visiting Nepal in early June, I.K. Gujral and his Nepali
counterpart agreed that at the next meeting of the foreign
secretaries to be held in two months, all issues of bilateral
interest including those related to the 1950 treaty would be
discussed.
</P>
<P>
Thapa said at the meeting to be held in New Delhi on August 19,
Nepal will put forth its views on the treaty.
</P>
<P>
A consultative committee of experts coordinated by the Foreign
Ministry has been formed with a view to evolving national
consensus on the 1950 treaty, the minister said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970812.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
