Shevardnadze thanked Yeltsin for his efforts to bring the two
sides together, Georgian presidential press service told the
Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
Primakov also called Shevardnadze, telling him that he would be
in the Georgian capital on Thursday, Interfax said.
</P>
