both sides together for negotiations aimed at resolving the
conflict, but no date has been set.
</P>
<P>
At issue is the degree of autonomy both parties will accept.
Separatists in Abkhazia drove out the Georgian army and 300,000
ethnic Georgian civilians in a 1992-93 war and proclaimed
independence. Georgia insists that the Black Sea province must
remain part of Georgia. 
