<HEADLINE> Thai Aviation Body OKs Special Fares for 6 States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Civil Aviation Commission of
Thailand has approved special fares for direct flights operated by
seven airlines of six countries, according to a report available
here today.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at a commission meeting on Monday chaired
by Thai Transport and Communications Minister Suwat Liptapallop.
</P>
<P>
According to the special fares, passengers will be charged 100
U.S. dollars if they travel less than 1,000 miles, 350 dollars for
1,000-1,200 miles, 400 dollars for 1,200-1,400 miles, 450 dollars
for 1,400-1,600 dollars, and 800 dollars for up to 3,000 miles.
</P>
<P>
The airlines involved will be Thai Airways International, China
Southern Airline, China's Yunnan Airlines, Myanmar Airways
International, Royal Air Cambodge, Lao Aviation and Vietnam
Airlines.
</P>
