<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria's Inflation Stands at 3.7 Percent in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria's inflation in July
reached 3.7 percent and the annual inflation stood at 505.6
percent, a report of the National Statistics Institute (NSI) said
today.
</P>
<P>
In July, fruit prices registered the greatest increase of 53.8
percent, the report said, adding that prices of cooking oil,
cheese and milk went up by 30.7 percent, 14.1 percent and 13.2
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Statistics of the NSI also showed that prices of onion, potato,
tomato and lamb were down. Soft drinks became cheaper by an
average of 2.3 percent. Prices of strong drinks, however, saw an
increase of 23.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Prices of medicine and medical service were also up 7.4 percent
and 6.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
While the public transport fares and the air fares increased by
11.5 percent and 7.4 percent respectively, the rail ticket prices
fell by 11.9 percent, the report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
