<HEADLINE> Stock Reform In Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Qinghai
Province now has five of its state enterprises listed on the stock
market and has raised 540 million yuan (65 million US dollars)
from that.
</P>
<P>
The Qinghai Department Store, Sanpu Pharmaceutical Co., Qinghai
Shanchuan, Qinghai Gelatin Co., and Tongren Aluminium Co. earned a
combined profit of 104.56 million yuan (12.6 million US dollars)
last year.
</P>
<P>
Their assets to debt ratio has dropped from 63.3 to 34.5
percent and they have all become pillar enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Encouraged by these intial successes, Qinghai has adopted some
market-oriented practices to turn 1,602 enterprises into
share-issuing companies, with registered capital of some three
billion yuan (361.45 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The province has selected another two businesses to be listed
on the stock market by the end of this year. 
</P>
