<HEADLINE> Guangdong Customs Seizes 723,000 Pirated VCDs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese customs officers have
seized about 723,000 pirated video CDs from a ship near Guangzhou,
capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Customs officials said the number of the confiscated VCDs,
including some 370,000 that are pornographic, was the largest ever
reported in the country.
</P>
<P>
An investigation showed that the ship belonged to a sea
transportation company out of the city of Jinjiang in Fujian
Province, and was run by a man surnamed Cai.
</P>
<P>
Cai was apprehended on August 5 while transferring the illegal
goods from one boat to another on the waters near Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong customs has confiscated more than 1.5 million pirated
VCDs this year since it intensified campaigns to protect
intellectual property rights. 
</P>
