<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Hold Township Elections in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
decided to hold the countrywide township elections, along with
election of village councils, in December this year instead of
September as scheduled earlier, cabinet sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting chaired by Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina on Monday,
the cabinet approved an Election Commission proposal to hold the
township elections in December.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, the cabinet decision to change the
scheduled was based on an opinion given by the Election Commission
which said that voters and others concerned would face
inconvenience if elections were held during September's rainy
weather.
</P>
<P>
The proposed township elections would be held between December
1 and 31 this year in a total of 4,671 townships in Bangladesh.
</P>
