<HEADLINE> Indonesia Donates Aid for Children Around the World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government has
donated 200,000 U.S. dollars worth of financial and food aid for
children around the world through the World Food Program (WFP, an
official said.
</P>
<P>
The aid was symbolically presented by the Agriculture Ministry
to the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) Representative
Office for Indonesia in Bandung, West Java, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The aid consisted of 54,327 dollars in cash and non-financial
support such as tea and vegetable oil, according to reports
reaching here today from Bandung.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia has allocated 2.7 million dollars in total for the
1997-98 period to help children around the world who lack
nutrients caused by conflicts and problems in their countries.
</P>
<P>
Quoting a research of the U.S. Agriculture Department, the
official from the Agriculture Ministry said there still would be
800 million people who lack of food and earnings by 2005.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the WFP headquarters had suggested Indonesia to ship
its donation to Africa and distribute them to the Egypt and Sudan
peoples.
</P>
<P>
The 1997 human development report issued by the UNDP showed
that in some African countries the number of poor people was still
higher than the other places.  
</P>
</TEXT>
