<HEADLINE> Romanian Alpinist Conquers Nanga Barbat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Romanian alpinist Mihai
Cioroianu conquered the 8,125-meter Nanga Barbat peak of the
Himalaya-Karakoram Range, confirmed the Romanian Alpinism
Federation here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Cioroianu, the second Romanian who overtook the peak, spent 16
hours with other four Spaniards to reach the top at 20:15 on July
20.
</P>
<P>
One Spaniard died and another injured during their journey back
to the base.
</P>
<P>
Romanian Gabriel Stana and Razvan Petcu missed when they
attempted the peak last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
