<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Record Dry Period For Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Although the threat of floods on
the Yellow River cannot yet be completely written off, it is much
more likely that the China's second longest river will witness a
record dry period this year, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
The lower section of the river has dried up for six years
mainly because of the drought in North China. It dried up last
year for a record 136 days, but the record is likely to be broken
in the next two days because there will not be enough rain to
cause the resumption of the flow of water on the lower reaches,
the paper quoted experts as saying.
</P>
<P>
The dried-up river will threaten up to 52 million people, more
than 7.4 million hectares of sown areas of crops, 40 percent of
which are irrigated high-yield areas.
</P>
<P>
One of the major factors causing the dry-up is the declining
volume of water in the river in the last few years, particularly
on its lower reaches, according to experts with the Ministry of
Water Resources.
</P>
<P>
At the Huayuankou Hydrological Station near Zhengzhou in Henan
Province on the lower reaches, only 8.8 billion cubic meters of
water flowed into the river during the first seven months of this
year, which was 50 percent lower than in previous years.
</P>
<P>
The shortage of water in the river was made worse by the
ever-increasing demand for water by provinces on the lower
reaches, the experts said.
</P>
<P>
More than 460 million cubic meters of water or 49 percent of
the total volume reaching the lower section of the river in the
first flood crest early this month were diverted by Shandong and
Henan, two of the worst-hit provinces during this year's
drought. More than 90 percent of the water was used for farmland
irrigation.
</P>
<P>
The rest of the water was lost either due to leakages from the
river's watercourses or large amounts of sand carried by the
water. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970812.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
