<HEADLINE> Stock Volume Boosts Tax Payments in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Tax payments from the Caracas
stock market rocketed to 21.82 million U.S. dollars this year from
last year's 9.8 million dollars and 1.87 million dollars in 1995.
</P>
<P>
During this year's 145 days of operation, trade volume in the
stock exchange amounted to a record-breaking level of 3.48 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
It took the stock exchange only seven months and seven days to
top last year's total exchange amount of 3 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Last Thursday, the Caracas stock exchange saw the highest trade
volume ever experienced in the Venezuelan stock market's 50-year
history. Some 495.2 million dollars traded hands in this single
day, providing the country with 4.91 million dollars in taxes.
</P>
<P>
The Caracas stock market ranks fifth in Latin America's stock
exchanges. 
</P>
