<HEADLINE> Tibet Hooks up with National Mobile Telecom Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Lhasa, the capital of the Tibet
Autonomous Region, has linked with the national digital mobile
telecom network since the beginning of this month.
</P>
<P>
China's Ministry of Post and Telecommunications invested 20.3
million yuan (2.45 million US dollars) for the infrastructure
construction while the local telecom authorities raised five
million yuan for support facilities.
</P>
<P>
The local global system for mobile communications (GSM) network
adopted switching and transmission equipment made by Sweden's
Ericsson Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The initial capacity of the net is designed to provide service
for some 20,000 subscribers.
</P>
<P>
With the six base stations already operational, the net now can
serve 4,700 users in downtown Lhasa, the airport and three
surrounding counties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
