<HEADLINE> Ming Tomb Found in Suburb of Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A tomb containing a brick tablet
engraved with a date from the Ming Dynasty (1368-1644) has been
found in the Fengtai district of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
According to Chinese archaeologists, the finding will be useful
in dating relics similar to those found in the tomb. The engraved
slab is the first of its kind ever excavated in the city, they
said.
</P>
<P>
The tablet, 51 cm high and 10 cm thick, was placed in the tomb
in May of 1527 by the son of the tomb's occupant.  
</P>
