<HEADLINE> Mercosur Briefs (2) Argentina-Chile Gas Pipeline Opening </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Buenos Aires -- Argentina President Carlos Menem and Chile
President Eduardo Frei opened officially the "Gasandes" gas
pipeline in the Argentinan province of Mendoza.
</P>
<P>
The 465-km long pipeline is a bilateral investment of 350
million dollars that connects station "Mora" south of Mendoza
with Santiago, Chile.

Menem Visits Chile
</P>
<P>
Santiago -- President of Argentina Carlos Menem visited
Chile on august 7 and 8.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Santiago, both countries signed accords on
several issues, including an agreement on bordering passes
regulations and another on cooperation in natural disasters and
deforestation.

Argentinan Army Performs Joint Practice With Chile
</P>
<P>
Buenos Aires -- The Argentinan army Chief of Staff Gen. Martin
Antonio Balza asserted joint practices between armies of Argentina
and Chile, to be held in 1998, come from a political decision.
</P>
<P>
Balza said this in a statement when he went with president
Carlos Menem for an official visit to Chile.

Brazil Boosts Manufacturing
</P>
<P>
Brasilia -- Manufacturing in brazil boosted 5.9 percent in
the first half 1997 in relation to the same period last year, a
Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statictics report said.
</P>
<P>
Industrial productions in June accounted for a 2.1 percent
increase against that recorded in May.

Venezuela's Join to Mercosur a Previous Step to AFTA
</P>
<P>
Caracas -- Venezuelan foreign minister Miguel Angel
burelli rivas said his country's join to mercosur is a previous
step towards the creation of the America Free Trade Area (AFTA).
</P>
<P>
"We consider our task is to be together with brazil in
Mercosur. There are problems between the trading bloc partners,
but they are getting along well, said Burelli.

Larger Oil Investments in Brazil are Expected
</P>
<P>
Rio de Janeiro -- Oil industry in Brazil will forecast 13
billion dollars in capital inflows next three years, said
the president of the state-run oil company Joel Renno.
</P>
<P>
Four billion are to be handed in by the private sector.
</P>
<P>
Officials expect Brazil to be energy self-sufficient by 2000
with a 1.5 million-barrels-a-day production, which would mean a
66.6 percent increase over current production of 900,000 barrels
a day, said Renno.

Mercosur-EU Enterprises Meeting
</P>
<P>
Montevideo -- Nearly 1,490 companies all over Mercosur, Chile,
Bolivia and the European Union contries subscribed to attend the
first "partenariat" EU-Mercosur, to be held in this city on
December 3, 4 and 5 1997, according to a press release.
</P>
<P>
The event, sponsored by the European Comission and organized
by the Chamber of Industries of Uruguay (CIU) is aimed to
strenghten the ties between the two blocs companies in order to
exchange technollogy, products and services through several
cooperation schemes such as joint ventures, technollogy exchange
agreements and training programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
