<HEADLINE> China's Advertising Watchdog to Check Medical Ads </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Television and newspaper ads
promoting medicine and medical equipment will be scrutinized
across the country.
</P>
<P>
The State Administration for Industry and Commerce, overseeing
China's advertising sector, will check and supervise the ads to
ensure the products and service to be "authentic, scientific and
legal", according to a report in today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
Contents of medical ads must be based on product directions and
standards approved by the Ministry of Health and local health
administrations, the report quoted a circular published by the
administration as saying.
</P>
<P>
Medical advertisements must carry warning labels to indicate
their differences from other non-advertised information, as
required by the law.
</P>
<P>
Companies violating the country's advertising laws will be
temporarily prohibited from advertising their products and subject
to penalties, the paper said.  
</P>
