<HEADLINE> Summer Festival Showcases Hui Folklore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A gala festival is currently
being held around the picturesque Shahu Lake to display the
colorful folklore of the Hui ethnic group of the Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia, located in northwest China, is the only autonomous
region of ethnic Hui people, known as Chinese Muslims.
</P>
<P>
Tourists attending the summer event, which runs through August,
will have the opportunity to enjoy traditional Hui songs and
dances, see a wedding ceremony, a performance of the martial art
wushu, dragon boat races and other sports competitions popular
among the Hui.
</P>
<P>
Other highlights for visitors include camel rides, parachuting,
boating, and sliding down a sandy hill on the lake bank.
</P>
<P>
The lake area is an hour's bus ride from Yinchuan, the capital
city of the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region. 
</P>
