decline was the largest of the year.
</P>
<P>
Mainichi:
</P>
<P>
-- The Administrative Reform Council, a panel of the Japanese
government, agreed Monday that ministries and agencies should be
reorganized under eight administrative categories, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Asahi, Mainichi, Nihon Keizai:
</P>
<P>
-- Japan's ruling Liberal Democratic Party announced Monday it
would seek to raise the maximum fine for banks involved with
Sokaiya corporate racketeers to 200 million yen (about 1.73
million dollars). 
</P>
