<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Sell Soviet Aircraft Carrier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Ukrainian Cabinet has decided
to sell a Soviet aircraft carrier, the Ukraine National News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paperwork for the tender of the uncompleted "Varyag"
carrier will be ready by the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
"Varyag," ordered by the former Soviet navy, was built by the
Pontic Navy Yard in the Black Sea port of Mykolaiv, Ukraine's
major shipbuilding center.
</P>
<P>
The revenues from the sale will be remitted to the Pontic Navy
Yard to replenish its funds and offset losses caused by the
300-meter-long ship's maintenance.
</P>
<P>
Since the political disintegration of the Soviet Union in 1991,
there have been several attempts to sell the ship.
</P>
<P>
Last April, the Pontic Navy Yard announced that it had started
formal procedures to sell "Varyag" to a British company as scrap
metal, but the deal was never finalized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
