<HEADLINE> Romanian Army Values PLA Friendship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian army believes a
friendly relationship with the Chinese People's Liberation Army
(PLA) is of great value, a senior Romanian military officer said
today.
</P>
<P>
Secretary of State of the Ministry of Defense Constantin
Degeratu made the remark during a meeting with Zhou Ziyu, deputy
director of the General Political Department of the PLA.
</P>
<P>
Zhou and a PLA delegation arrived here Monday on a goodwill
visit to this central European country.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Degeratu, who is also chief of the general
staff of Romania's armed forces, spoke highly of the policy of
reform and opening-up to the outside world adopted by the Chinese
government.
</P>
<P>
China, one of the fastest growing countries in the world, is
playing an increasingly important role in international society,
Degeratu said.
</P>
<P>
Constanti Dudu Ionescu, another secretary of state of the
Ministry of Defense also present at the meeting, said the
impending visit by Romanian President Emil Constantinescu to China
would help promote friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The PLA delegation is expected to visit Romania's military
facilities outside the capital on Tuesday. After leaving Romania,
the delegation will visit Hungary. 
