<HEADLINE> Telecoms Aims To Raise Staff Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Telecoms officials and experts
from Asia-Pacific Economic Co-operation (Apec) member countries
and regions gathered in Beijing to discuss co-operation and
exchange in human resources development (HRD), a step towards
achieving the goal of the Asia-Pacific Information Infrastructure
(APII), today's "China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
Hosted by China's Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications,
the '97 Apec TEL HRD International Symposium from August 11-13
will include discussions on enhancing co-operation among Apec
member economies in the HRD field to promote APII.
</P>
<P>
The symposium will also cover exchanges of expertise of
achievements in the areas of education and training. The Ministry
of Posts and Telecoms introduced an employee quality campaign
aimed at raising the quality of human resources and speeding up
reform in education and training.
</P>
<P>
There are about 1.2 million postal and telecoms staff in China,
whose overall quality still lags behind the requirements of post
and telecoms development, the paper says. 
</P>
