<HEADLINE> Ibero-American Agricultural Forum Opens in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- An Ibero-American agricultural
forum opened today in Venezuela's eastern city of Maturin for
discussions of the process of economic globalization and the
development of agriculture in Ibero-America.
</P>
<P>
Venezuelan President Rafael Caldera opened the event by saying
that agriculture has an undeniable importance to the life and
sustainable development of all nations.
</P>
<P>
Caldera stressed that during the remaining years of the 20th
century and initial years of the 21st century, the technological
revolution and the globalization process have strong effects on
people's life, specially agriculture and cattle breeding.
</P>
<P>
This obliges us to face new risks, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said the forum is a good stage to prepare for the 7th
Ibero-American Summit to be held in Margarita Island, Venezuela in
November.
</P>
<P>
The fighting against hunger and food shortages is one of the
most important issues on the forum's agenda.
</P>
<P>
Conclusions and accords reached at the forum will be taken to
the November summit.
</P>
<P>
The event is attended by ministers and representatives of
public and private institutions of agriculture and cattle breeding
from 21 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
