<HEADLINE> Nebiolo Criticize Athens Organizers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Prime Nebiolo, president of the
International Amateur Athletic Federation, said that the world
championships here would have been a "tragedy" as the organizers
failed to bring satisfied crowd on the stands in the opening days.
</P>
<P>
The championships could be a "tragedy" if the IAAF hadn't
stepped in to remedy the situation. "The organizing team wasn't up
to much, we found it mediocre." Nebiolo on Monday told the Greek
television channel Mega.
</P>
<P>
The IAAF Chief also mocked Athens' bid to host the 2004 Olympic
Games. Athens is competing against Rome -- backed by Nebiolo --
Stockholm, Cape Town and Buenos Aires.
</P>
<P>
"The Olympics can't resolve Greece's problems," he said.
</P>
<P>
But Evangelos Savramis, the head of the world championships
organizing committee, said: "The only thing Mr. Nebiolo did was to
continually create problems."
</P>
<P>
Savramis firmly put the poor crowd on the IAAF, saying that
Nebiolo refused to allow them to put the event back a month
despite it falling in the middle of the tradition Greek holiday
period.
</P>
<P>
Athens mayor Dimitris Avramopoulos complained that Nebiolo was
behaving like the honorary president of the Rome bid for the 2004
games. 
</P>
