<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 11 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks ended mixed
today with the Dow Jones industrials getting out of a 50-point
loss but technology shares losing ground.
</P>
<P>
The Dow rose 30.89 to 8,062.11 at the closing. The Dow index
lost 156 points on Friday and 71 points on Thursday, slipping from
its all-time closing high of 8,259.31 last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues slightly outnumbered advancers.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume totaled 480.34 million shares, down from 561.33
million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 3.46 to 937.00, and
the NYSE composite index rose 1.42 to 485.21.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index fell 11.81 to 1,586.71, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index fell 1.80 to 644.35.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year Treasury was up slightly for the day and yielding
6.63 percent.  
