<HEADLINE> Jetliner Hijacker Sentenced to 20 Years in Prison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Sadd'o Mohammed Ibrahim
Intissar, who hijacked a Cuban-bound Spanish jet liner to Miami
last year, was sentenced today to 20 years in prison.
</P>
<P>
He was convicted in U.S. District Court April 25 of hijacking
an Iberia Airlines jumbo jet that was en route from Madrid, Spain,
to Havana July 26, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Brandishing a pair of scissors and a fake bomb, he forced the
plane with 286 people aboard to Miami. 
</P>
